                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d257">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.71293/52: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1" type="to"
                            >Johnson</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-12T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 12, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>311. Department’s 291, August 27, 3 p.m.<note n="53" xml:id="d257fn53">Not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Under date September 7, the Post Office Department issued orders
                        suspending parcel post service and money order business to and from
                        Manchuria, excepting Kwangtung Leased Territory. War Department is
                        suggesting to Philippines postal administration similar action.<note n="54"
                            xml:id="d257fn54">On September 21, the War Department notified the
                            Department of State that Governor General of the Philippine Islands had
                            reported the taking of similar action there (811.71293/56).</note>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>For the present at least, ordinary mail matter received in this country
                        bearing “Manchoukuo” postage is being delivered without penalty to the
                        addressee.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_CWR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
